- And... that Christmas tree. This definitely is the Santa, I am telling you. 
 - Okay.

46
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,020
Hurry.

47
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:17,840
What?

48
00:08:24,690 --> 00:08:27,280
 You crazy wench!  If you broadcast,

49
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:32,010
 I will throw you into the fiery pits of Hell, you broadcast jerks!

50
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:35,360
- Broadcast station jerks? 
 - Ah!

51
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:38,140
We meant to interview for the opening of the Fiery Pit sauna,

52
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:43,150
- but it looks like we came here by mistake.   You must have a daughter since I see some girl's clothes.
 - Yeah.

53
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:48,490
Camera.

54
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:51,750
Why?

55
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:54,720
- Hurry, run, run! 
 - Why?

56
00:08:55,770 --> 00:08:57,530
Sic'em!

57
00:08:59,050 --> 00:09:02,010
- Hurry! 
 - Hurry up!

58
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,760

59
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:12,510
Hurry!

60
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:32,870
- Car key! 
 - Car key.  Uh!

61
00:09:33,870 --> 00:09:37,280
- I don't have the car key! 
 - Why not?!

62
00:09:49,940 --> 00:09:53,080
- Hold on tight.  
 - Yes, Sir.

63
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:05,370
I'll go this way, so you check that place.

64
00:10:05,370 --> 00:10:06,930
Right.

65
00:10:07,910 --> 00:10:09,870
Sunji!

66
00:10:09,870 --> 00:10:12,180
Kong Sunji!

67
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:14,610
- Sunji! 
  - Over here! I'm here!

68
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:17,540
 Cha Dohyun, I'm in here!

69
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:21,540
Let go! Let go of this!

70
00:10:21,540 --> 00:10:23,670
Go away!

71
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:25,530
Kong Sunji, are you in there?

72
00:10:25,530 --> 00:10:30,410
Cha Dohyun, hurry up and do something!

73
00:10:31,220 --> 00:10:34,630
Come here! Come here, good job.

74
00:10:34,630 --> 00:10:38,110
Come here. What a good dog.

75
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:40,210
You can come out now.

76
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:46,370
Hey, where's the PD?

77
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:48,170
The PD?

78
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:51,080
Detective Cha!

79
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,980
You really are something.

80
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:58,550
The police are here, so I'll talk to the chief.

81
00:10:58,550 --> 00:11:01,000
Oh, he's coming.

82
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:05,520
- Is it him? 
 - Yeah, it's him.

83
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:07,650
This punk's the Santa, right?

84
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,760
What to do? It's not him.

85
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:12,540
What are you talking about? Yes, he is.

86
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:16,280
Here, look. The scar on his face and his eyebrows.

87
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,720
There's even a mole by his lips, it's him!

88
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:23,020
The thing is, he wasn't present when the incident occurred.

89
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:26,180
He wasn't there? Are you sure?

90
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:30,320
Wrong again? How many tries is this going to take?

91
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:34,380
I was certain of it this time.

92
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:41,020
He's not the Santa, but he has a location tracker for sexual predators.

93
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:43,350
I've never done that.

94
00:11:43,350 --> 00:11:47,390
The kids came on their own to see the dogs.

95
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:03,590
That's why you're a criminal, you bastard.

96
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:12,450
Where the hell is he?

97
00:12:13,410 --> 00:12:18,760

98
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,050
 I'm hungry.

99
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:38,180
 A rabbit?

100
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:39,230
 Did I just eat a rabbit raw?

101
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:54,500
 I am no longer human.

102
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:05,380
 If this is my new life, I'd rather die.

103
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,150
 I want to die, but I can't.

104
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:34,880
 I'm a living corpse. A zombie.

105
00:14:39,780 --> 00:14:43,020
 How did I become a zombie?

106
00:14:45,630 --> 00:14:47,910
 Can I go back to being a human?

107
00:14:47,910 --> 00:14:50,200
 Human? You?

108
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,820
 A passing dog would laugh if it heard you call yourself human.

109
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:57,240
Detective, this is... this is defamation of character.

110
00:14:57,240 --> 00:15:01,140
I... I'm going to sue this woman for assault.

111
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:03,090
How could she give a double nose bleed to an innocent man—

112
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:04,430
You're an innocent man?

113
00:15:04,430 --> 00:15:09,240
You're an innocent man, but you carry a location tracker as an accessory?

114
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:11,330
What kind of a crazy-ass are you?

115
00:15:11,330 --> 00:15:14,410
- Are you done? 
 - Do I look like I'm done?

116
00:15:14,410 --> 00:15:16,320
Do you think I'd be done?

117
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,480
- You're worth less than a dog. 
 - Hey.

118
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,750
Don't be rude, come on.

119
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:24,100
You're worth less than a dog, so how could you raise one?

120
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:26,330
You better not raise any dogs from now on!

121
00:15:26,330 --> 00:15:28,280
You scumbag!

122
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:32,920

123
00:15:35,410 --> 00:15:37,520
My phone.

124
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:41,100
Oh, right. That dog.

125
00:15:49,890 --> 00:15:54,100
 Something has definitely happened.

126
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:59,260
 Either the world has ended, or a zombie virus has spread.

127
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:05,150
 For now, I'll go to the village and see what's happened.

128
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:12,170
 I'm in a rush, but why am I so freaking slow?

129
00:16:33,790 --> 00:16:37,150
Where did I drop it?

130
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:51,400
 Go away.

131
00:16:53,310 --> 00:16:55,420
 I said, go away!

132
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:27,570
I definitely heard something around here.

133
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:33,340
 It's a human!

134
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:39,920
 Why is that human fine?

135
00:17:45,780 --> 00:17:48,830
  - Is... someone there? 
 - Damn it.

136
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:55,910
 - I must retreat.  
 - Excuse me. Who are you?

137
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,710
 Why am I so slow?

138
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:08,490
Excuse me, that hoodie is mine.

139
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:12,500
- Do you live here? 
 -  What?

140
00:18:13,190 --> 00:18:15,950
 This freaking flashlight...

141
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:20,150
Sir, you can keep my hoodie.

142
00:18:20,150 --> 00:18:22,730
But can you give me the phone in the pocket?

143
00:18:22,730 --> 00:18:24,680
 In the pocket?

144
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:28,010
I'll take it.

145
00:18:28,010 --> 00:18:29,930
 No.

146
00:18:33,870 --> 00:18:36,230
 What is this smell?

147
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:39,280
 Where is this sweet smell...

148
00:18:44,970 --> 00:18:48,840
Hello? Yeah, I found it.

149
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:54,520
Hold on, I'll call you back.

150
00:18:57,270 --> 00:19:03,200
Sir, this is all I have.

151
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:08,360
Take this and go to a sauna.

152
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:13,640
Also, please receive treatment for your alcoholism.

153
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:17,400
You might die from it, so you have to be careful.

154
00:19:20,470 --> 00:19:22,430
Here.

155
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:30,240
Then, goodbye.

156
00:19:32,870 --> 00:19:37,350
 Did I just try to eat a human?

157
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:43,160
 No way. Is this the natural instinct of a zombie?

158
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:46,870
 No.

159
00:19:46,870 --> 00:19:50,520
 I cannot live as a zombie who eats humans.

160
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:56,570
 If I don't want to eat humans, I'll have to eat something.

161
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,800
 Bird eggs should be okay, right?

162
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:07,640
 I'm sorry. Just one.

163
00:20:16,320 --> 00:20:19,510
 This freaking zombie thing.

164
00:20:37,390 --> 00:20:39,930
 I've been starving for three days.

165
00:20:40,980 --> 00:20:46,870
 When I'm hungry for too long, I lose my senses.

166
00:21:05,460 --> 00:21:10,690
 And when I wake up, someone has been sacrificed.

167
00:21:14,890 --> 00:21:19,650

Beef Tripe Stew? What is this?

168
00:21:26,650 --> 00:21:28,550
Beef tripe really is the best.

169
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:33,440
Maybe I should quit and open a tripe restaurant.

170
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:36,550
Don't you think I'll do really well?

171
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:39,650
Where the hell is this Santa guy?

172
00:21:39,650 --> 00:21:44,640
I also have experience doing colonoscopies.

173
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,980
You know what the funny thing is?

174
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:49,840
The more bad guys I find,

175
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:55,740
the more only similar suspects come up. Super close.

176
00:22:02,450 --> 00:22:04,210
I should've become a cop.

177
00:22:04,210 --> 00:22:07,100
Then you would've been fired within a month.

178
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:09,420
You didn't have to face any settlement charges this time?

179
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:11,560
Of course, I did.

180
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:15,230
I begged for three-month installment payments and got an agreement.

181
00:22:15,230 --> 00:22:17,420
Three months?

182
00:22:17,420 --> 00:22:19,580
Does your sister know?

183
00:22:21,170 --> 00:22:22,900
She'll go crazy if she finds out.

184
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:27,360
On top of that, I even lost my hoodie.

185
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:30,320
It's actually hers.

186
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:32,320
Are you sure you lost it?

187
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:36,000
I am sure you probably gave it to someone as charity.

188
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:41,050
A couple of days ago, I went back to find my phone,

189
00:22:41,050 --> 00:22:43,730
but there was an alcoholic there.

190
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:46,900
He was walking towards me barefoot.

191
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:54,220
If only I had more money, I would've given him more. I felt so bad.

192
00:22:54,950 --> 00:22:58,080
You don't have the time to pity others right now.

193
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:01,330
You said you haven't even paid off for your last gangster-like behavior.

194
00:23:01,330 --> 00:23:05,010
Lower your voice, or my sister will...

195
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:08,330
You still haven't paid off the settlement for last month's gangster-like behavior?

196
00:23:09,080 --> 00:23:11,570
That's not it, Sis.

197
00:23:11,570 --> 00:23:14,830
I told you to lower your voice. You're so dead.

198
00:23:14,830 --> 00:23:18,610
Is it the job of the journalist for 70-Minute Chase to beat up people?

199
00:23:18,610 --> 00:23:23,100
Why do you always use your monthly paycheck to pay for these settlements?

200
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:26,610
Sis, I'm going to pay it back soon. There's not much left.

201
00:23:26,610 --> 00:23:28,130
You should hit me, too.

202
00:23:28,130 --> 00:23:31,920
I'll at least get the money you owe me for living fees that way, hm?

203
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:35,780
Sis, come on. You're making Bora uncomfortable.

204
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:42,540
Don't worry about me, we're not strangers. You can continue, Sunyoung.

205
00:23:42,540 --> 00:23:45,460
If it's 70-Minute Chase, you should only chase for 70 minutes.

206
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:50,880
Why the hell do you always chase around day after day and only get paid about as much as a dried anchovy's crap-filled head?!

207
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:55,750
Forget about reporting others, I should just report this crappy broadcast station!

208
00:23:57,580 --> 00:23:59,260
I'm sorry.

209
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:06,630
I'll pay you as soon as I'm done eating, so wait just a few minutes.

210
00:24:14,380 --> 00:24:16,460
Where's the kimchi?

211
00:24:22,410 --> 00:24:26,300
Of course, black bean noodles must be eaten with kimchi or yellow pickled radish.

212
00:24:26,300 --> 00:24:29,540
My boss said you have to pay for the kimchi, too.

213
00:24:29,540 --> 00:24:33,040
You should just order kimchi stew at this rate.

214
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,150
Give me a coupon.

215
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:46,130
Friend, where are you from?

216
00:24:46,130 --> 00:24:49,850
- I am from Yanbian. 
 - Yanbian.

217
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:54,610
If I were to open up the first overseas branch,

218
00:24:54,610 --> 00:24:57,450
I was planning on opening it in Yanbian, China.

219
00:24:57,450 --> 00:25:00,320
Do you even have any customers here?

220
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:05,330
I heard that Detective Kim Mooyoung's office across the street does better business.

221
00:25:05,330 --> 00:25:09,150
There is a rumor that Kim Mooyoung will soon be leaving Gangrim City.

222
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:12,890
If that happens, the only number in this Gangrim City,

223
00:25:12,890 --> 00:25:16,110
will be me, Lee Sungrok.

224
00:25:16,110 --> 00:25:18,900
You can leave the empty bowls out front.

225
00:25:21,130 --> 00:25:23,270
How much does President Kang pay you?

226
00:25:23,270 --> 00:25:24,920
I get paid the standard.

227
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:30,500
Then, how do you feel about working with me, Lee Sungrok?

228
00:25:34,630 --> 00:25:36,430
I don't.

229
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:43,220
- Mr. President? 
 - Did you go all the way to Yanbian to deliver black-bean noodles?!

230
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:45,750
 If this is how you're going to work, don't bother showing up tomorrow!

231
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:49,430
 You punk, I took pity because of your current situation but you should be grateful!

232
00:25:49,430 --> 00:25:53,720
 - I have plenty of others— 
  - I quit.

233
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,100
What are you doing?

234
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:57,500
He doesn't know how valuable people are.

235
00:25:57,500 --> 00:26:02,690
To use someone fluent in both Chinese and Korean in this way...

236
00:26:02,690 --> 00:26:04,710
What a shame.

237
00:26:04,710 --> 00:26:07,850
With me, Lee Sungrok, it won't be a boss vs. underling,

238
00:26:07,850 --> 00:26:11,420
but rather you will work as a person to person.

239
00:26:11,420 --> 00:26:14,260
I will pay you the standard and will even provide you with room and board.

240
00:26:14,260 --> 00:26:16,620
Even room and board?

241
00:26:16,620 --> 00:26:19,870
On top of that, if I open a chain office in Yanbian,

242
00:26:19,870 --> 00:26:23,930
I will even think about making you the branch manager.

243
00:26:23,930 --> 00:26:28,800
- I can tell just by looking at you that you are branch manager material. 
 - Even a branch manager in Yanbian?

244
00:26:32,180 --> 00:26:37,420
This reminds me of my mother in my hometown.  I haven't seen her in over a year.

245
00:26:37,420 --> 00:26:41,480
I know this is not good manners, but how old are you, sir?

246
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:46,690
Boss, please speak comfortably. I'm 28 this year.

247
00:26:54,070 --> 00:26:56,050
- Are you serious? 
 - Yes.

248
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:59,270
I was born in '92, so I'm turning 28 this year.

249
00:26:59,270 --> 00:27:01,690
You suffered quite a lot after you arrived in Korea.

250
00:27:01,690 --> 00:27:05,250
Just what on earth is happening in the Republic of Korea?

251
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,630

252
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:15,870
 A zombie virus has spread here, so take us to Busan immediately.

253
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:28,630
 Stay right here and don't move.  I will finish it quickly.

254
00:27:28,630 --> 00:27:30,470
 Be careful, Oppa.

